/ -- Root File System
/bin -- Essential User Binaries
/boot -- Static Boot
/cdrom -- Mount Point for CDROMs *
/dev -- Device Files
/etc -- Host-Specific System Configuration
/home -- User Home Directories
/lib -- Essential Shared Libraries and Kernel Modules
/lost+found -- Recovered Files/Kdump Files
/media -- Removable Media
/mnt -- Temporary Mount Points
/opt -- Optional Packages
/proc -- Kernel and Process Files
/root -- Root Home Directory
/run -- Application State Files
/sbin -- System Administration Binaries
/selinux -- SELinux Virtual File System
/srv -- Service Data
/tmp -- Temporary Files
/usr -- User Binaries and Read-Only Data
/var -- Variable Data Files
DETAILED:
/bin -- commands for the regular & super user
/sbin -- commands for the super user
/boot -- holds important files for boot-up process, including Linux Kernel
/etc -- contains application's configuration files
/home -- home directory for regular user
/mnt -- temp. mount directory for mounting file systems
/opt -- contains third party application software
/var -- contents of this file are expected to grow
/etc/sudoers -- config file for root access
/etc/passwd -- holds acct. information
/etc/shadow -- holds password information
/etc/group -- holds group information
